Itau Takes BofA Economist Castro Cunha to Manage Fixed-Income Securities

-- B y   G a b r i e l l e   C o p p o l a
-- 
2011-04-07T15:42:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/itau-takes-castro-cunha-from-bank-of-america-to-manage-fixed-income-assets.html
Itau Asset Management hired Virgilio Castro Cunha, the former head of Brazil economics and fixed-
income strategy at  Bank of America Corp. (BAC)  in  Sao Paulo , according
to a person familiar with the matter.  Castro Cunha will work for Itau, Brazil’s second-largest
asset manager, as a fixed-income money manager in Sao Paulo,
said the person, who asked not to be identified in accordance
with company policy. He holds a master’s degree in economics
from the University of Chicago.  Rinat Rond, a Bank of America spokeswoman in New York, said
the bank doesn’t comment on personnel matters. An official in
the press department at Itau Asset Management in Sao Paulo
declined to comment. Castro Cunha couldn’t be reached for
comment.  BB DTVM SA, the asset-management unit of Banco do Brasil
SA, is the largest money manager in  Brazil , according to Anbima,
the country’s capital markets association.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gabrielle Coppola in Sao Paulo at 
 gcoppola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  